53.081.  Land sales report to tax commission. — The assessor in each county, except counties of the first class having a charter form of government, in addition to other duties provided by law, shall each calendar month verify ten sales of real property made within his county during that month and shall make a report of these sales to the state tax commission.  The report of each such sale shall contain:
  (1)  The name of the grantor;
  (2)  The name of the grantee;
  (3)  The amount of consideration when available; and if not available then the assessor shall reassess the property;
  (4)  The amount at which the property is currently assessed;
  (5)  Whether or not the sale involved newly constructed property; and
  (6)  The name of the person verifying the sale.
(L. 1969 3d Ex. Sess. S.B. 1) 
Effective 9-01-70
